{
    "name":  "Prime Rib Soup",
    "instructions":  "1. Place the ribs in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the meat is falling from the bones, about 2 hours.  \n\n2. Remove ribs and allow to cool. Trim the meat from the ribs and cut into bite-sized pieces; refrigerate.  \n\n3. Continue simmering broth until reduced; refrigerate until the fat congeals to the top.  \n\n4. Skim and discard the congealed fat.  \n\n5. Pour broth into a saucepan along with meat trimmings, beef stock, potato, carrots, mushrooms, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.  \n\n6. Sprinkle with chives to serve.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Simmer ribs in water for 2 hours until meat is tender.  \n\n2. Trim meat and refrigerate.  \n\n3. Simmer broth, then refrigerate to remove fat.  \n\n4. Skim off fat.  \n\n5. Cook broth with beef, stock, vegetables, salt, and pepper.  \n\n6. Serve with chives.",
